{"Body":"<p>Wikitionary shows a PIE word <a href=\"http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Appendix%3aProto-Indo-European/m%C3%A9h%E2%82%82t%C4%93r\" rel=\"nofollow\">*<em>méh₂tēr</em></a> but I never seen this word spelled with a laryngeal. There was a long vowel there but how is it correct to analyze it to be *<em>-eh₂-</em> rather than just *<em>ā</em>?</p>\n", "Id":"1314", "LastEditorUserId":"624", "AcceptedAnswerId":"4689", "Title":"What is the evidence for laryngeal in *méh₂tēr?", "CreationDate":"2012-01-22T11:19:39.570", "OwnerUserId":"624", "PostTypeId":"1", "Tags":"<comparative-linguistics><proto-indo-european><vocabulary>", "AnswerCount":"1", "comments":[], "LastEditDate":"2012-01-22T12:41:09.577", "LastEditedUser":{"UpVotes":"81", "DownVotes":"60", "Id":"624", "AccountId":"407237", "Views":"34", "Reputation":"1743", "CreationDate":"2011-12-28T07:24:31.420", "DisplayName":"Anixx", "LastAccessDate":"2014-01-18T10:33:34.597"}, "ViewCount":"150", "LastActivityDate":"2013-10-10T20:53:42.073", "Score":"3", "CommentCount":"4", "OwnerUser":{"UpVotes":"81", "DownVotes":"60", "Id":"624", "AccountId":"407237", "Views":"34", "Reputation":"1743", "CreationDate":"2011-12-28T07:24:31.420", "DisplayName":"Anixx", "LastAccessDate":"2014-01-18T10:33:34.597"}}